'Aldermen'' or ''board of aldermen'' shall include the board of election commissioners or election commission of any city having such a board or commission, as to all matters coming within the scope of their powers and duties, and as to such matters shall not apply to the city council of such city. https://malegislature.gov/Laws/GeneralLaws/PartI/TitleVIII/Chapter50/Section1

Executive – Expenditures related to the executive operations of the community.
Reporting units:
121 Mayor
122 Selectmen
123 Town or City Manager
129 Other Executive

"Selectmen are a town’s executive officers. Voters elect them to the Board of Selectmen, which usually has three or five members. Selectmen are authorized to call a Town Meeting provided that they have posted a warrant. In small towns, the Board of Selectmen runs the town and supervises town workers. In larger towns, the Board of Selectmen picks and supervises a person, who, in turn, runs the town and supervises town workers. Depending on the town, that person has various authority, duties, and title. That person is known as the town manager, town administrator, executive secretary, or administrative secretary." https://www.sec.state.ma.us/cis/cistwn/twnidx.htm
